260–Male":"1260–Deceased","1260–Female":"1260–Deceased","1277–Female":"1277–Deceased","1243–Male":"1243–Deceased","1245–Female":"1245–Deceased","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1243":"1243","1260":"1260","Hesketh,Croston,Lancashire,England.":"Croston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","Heskeith, Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hesketh","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cheshire): habitational name from Hesketh (Lancashire), Hesketh Grange in Felixkirk (North Yorkshire), or Hesket in the Forest (Cumberland). The placenames derive from Old Norse <i>hestr</i> ‘horse, stallion’ + <i>skeith</i> ‘course, track, race course’. The ancient Scandinavians were fond of horse-racing and horse-fighting, and introduced both pastimes to England."],"variants":[{"name":"Heskett","meanings":["English (Cumberland and Lancashire): variant of   Hesketh  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert Hesketh was born in 1260, in Croston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Richard Hesketh, was 17 and his mother, Annabel de Stafford, was 15. He married Mrs. Robert Hesketh in 1277, in Croston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1260–":"1260–Surnud","1260–Male":"1260–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1277–Female":"1277–Surnud","1243–Male":"1243–Surnud","1245–Female":"1245–Surnud","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1243":"1243","1260":"1260","Hesketh,Croston,Lancashire,England.":"Croston, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Heskeith, Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1260–":"1260–Kuollut","1260–Male":"1260–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1277–Female":"1277–Kuollut","1243–Male":"1243–Kuollut","1245–Female":"1245–Kuollut","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1243":"1243","1260":"1260","Hesketh,Croston,Lancashire,England.":"Croston, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Heskeith, Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1260–":"1260–Décédé","1260–Male":"1260–Décédé","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","1277–Female":"1277–Décédée","1243–Male":"1243–Décédé","1245–Female":"1245–Décédée","1245":"1245","1277":"1277","1243":"1243","1260":"1260","Hesketh,Croston,Lancashire,England.":"Croston, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Heskeith, Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert Hesketh est né en 1260, à Croston, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Richard Hesketh, avait 17 ans et sa mère, Annabel de Stafford, avait 15 ans. Il a épousé Mrs. Robert Hesketh en 1277, à Croston, Lancashire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"1260–":"1260–Verstorben","1260–Male":"1260–Verstorben","1260–Female":"1260–Verstorben","1277–Female":"1277–Verstorben","1243–Ma